"example, a contiguous ``(3, 4)`` array of type ``int16`` in C-order has "
"strides ``(8, 2)``.  This implies that to move from element to element in "
"memory requires jumps of 2 bytes. To move from row-to-row, one needs to jump "
"8 bytes at a time (``2 * 4``)."
